<h2>FAQs</h2>

<div class="faq">
    <h3>Can I make these wraps ahead of time?</h3>
    <p>Yes, you can prepare the wraps in advance and store them in an airtight container in the refrigerator for up to 3 days. When ready to use, simply reheat them in a skillet or microwave.</p>

    <h3>Can I freeze the wraps?</h3>
    <p>Absolutely! These wraps freeze well. Place parchment paper between each wrap to prevent sticking, and store them in a freezer-safe bag or container. They can be frozen for up to 2 months. Thaw and reheat as needed.</p>

    <h3>Are these wraps suitable for a vegan diet?</h3>
    <p>Yes, this recipe is entirely plant-based and suitable for vegans. Just ensure that any fillings you choose are also vegan-friendly.</p>

    <h3>Can I use other flours instead of chickpea flour?</h3>
    <p>While chickpea flour is the star of this recipe, you can experiment with other gluten-free flours like almond flour or coconut flour. However, the texture and flavor may vary.</p>
</div>

<h2>Conclusion</h2>

<p>Gluten-free, grain-free wraps made with chickpea flour are a fantastic addition to any diet. They are easy to make, highly nutritious, and incredibly versatile. Whether you're looking for a quick lunch option, a healthy snack, or a creative dinner idea, these wraps have got you covered. Give this recipe a try and discover the endless possibilities that chickpea flour has to offer. Happy cooking!</p>

